data.name: label10.Text
data.value: When in the Account Manager, and you want to add a new account to the system, you'll click 'Add Account'. When you do click that button. You'll be confronted with this window. This window is used for creating accounts specifically. Input a username, password, then leave the admin account checkbox either checked or unchecked, then click 'Create Account' and you would of created a new account on the system.

data.name: label9.Text
data.value: Upon clicking 'Account Manager' on the hub, you'll be greeted by this window. From here you may view all accounts stored in the system, add an account, delete an account, and demote or promote users from or to admin. All of these actions require you to select an account from the list before attempting to invoke the action.

data.name: label7.Text
data.value:
When you click on the Resolve button, you'll be greeted with this window.
The primary function is for the admin to write the resolution of the problem for similar problems that may occur in the future.
After you've filled out the description box, click 'Resolve' to update the re- port.

data.name: label6.Text
data.value: If you happen to be an engineer, and click on the 'Problems' button on the hub. Then you'll be met with this window. This windows displays all reports stored on the system. Excluding `Refresh`, you must select an item to use any of the other buttons. 'More Info' will bring up all the information on the selected report. 'Resolve' will bring up a form to add a resolution description, and 'Delete Report' will delete the report off of the system.

data.name: label5.Text
data.value: Reporting a problem is pretty easy. Simply specify the room where the problem is the severity of the problem, and the problem type, as well as a moderately sized description of the problem, and click submit.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value:
When you successfully login you will be met with this window.
This window is the hub. Account Manager and Problems are only accessible by administrator but 'Report a Problem' is accessible to a standard account. The log off button should be self explainatory as well.

data.name: label2.Text
data.value:
In order to log in you must first have an account. The standard admin account is: username: admin password: password1.
Once you have an account you input your username in the respective box, as well as your password too.
If you have forgot your password you can reset it by clicking the 'Forgot Password?' button.
